Right order of access privilege  is--

    `class SuperClass{
              void foo(){
        System.out.print(&quot;SuperClass&quot;);
         }
       class SubClass extends{

      //--default to default--//
             void foo(){
      System.out.print(&quot;SubClass&quot;);
       }
     //--default to protected--//

      protected void foo(){
      System.out.print(&quot;SubClass&quot;);
 
     //--default to public //

     public void foo(){
     System.out.print(&quot;SubClass&quot;);
     }` 

        **you make sure to preserve correct order while overriding **

