As you can see, `AffineTransformOp.filter()`, used in `scaleBilinear()`, is faster than the standard drawing method of `Graphics2D.drawImage()` in `scale2()`. Also BiCubic interpolation is the slowest, but gives the best results when expanding the image. (For performance, it should only be compared with `scaleBilinear()` and `scaleNearest().`) Bilinear seems to be better for shrinking the image, although it&#39;s a tough call. And NearestNeighbor is the fastest, with the worst results. Bilinear seems to be the best compromise between speed and quality. The `Image.getScaledInstance()`, called in the `questionable()` method, performed very poorly, and returned the same low quality as NearestNeighbor. (Performance numbers are only given for expanding the image.)

